result.name: Tenzen Japanese Restaurant

reviews.text: We had an excellent meal here after the Rugby Sevens.  A friend introduced me to the place and I will certainly return.  Good food, good atmosphere, warm & welcoming chef.
Fresh sashimi and great tempura seaweed codfish roe as well!!! Waitresses could be more friendly but extremely satisfied I got my sushi fix 😊🙏🏼

My favourite sushi restaurant by far. Food is always super fresh. They have a choose-your-own sushi option at lunch that my friends and I always order because it is incredible value for money (~$260 for 10pc - see photos). This restaurant has become a staple for everyone we come with.

First time to visit, totally surprise on the food quality for lunch in the Japanese restaurant. 

I ordered two sushi sets. WOR... So amazing. All the fish were really fresh. They were delicious and the food quality were better than the dinner of many Japanese restaurants. It was totally VFM (value for money)

4 sushi chefs were in the sushi bar. They were nice, friendly and chatted with customers. I also found many revisiting customers.

Fresh ingredients, a bit pricey, but you get what you paid. Able to sit n chat. The service was a bit lukewarm though, depending on individual staff members. Had to ask for utensils as only the basics were served. With such a price, I would be expecting better services.

HK sushi chef who can speak Japanese. Very friendly and attentive. Provide wide choices of sushi. This sushi restaurant is one of the few which local Japanese people would visit.
